  "body": "### What\r\n\r\nI am currently trying to migrate from a truffle project to Buidler -> https://github.com/mstable/mStable-contracts/pull/89\r\n\r\nAs you can see from the `buidler.config.ts`, the test suite is written in Typescript.\r\n\r\n### Issue\r\n\r\nRunning `yarn buidler coverage --network coverage --solcoverjs ./.solcover.js --testfiles test/**/Test*.ts --show-stack-traces` results in the following output:\r\n\r\n```\r\nError BDLR308: Unrecognized positional argument test/governance/TestDelayedClaimableGovernor.spec.ts\r\n\r\nError: BDLR308: Unrecognized positional argument test/governance/TestDelayedClaimableGovernor.spec.ts\r\n    at ArgumentsParser._parsePositionalParamArgs (/home/alex/projects/stability-labs/mstable/mStable-contracts/node_modules/@nomiclabs/buidler/src/internal/cli/ArgumentsParser.ts:271:13)\r\n    at ArgumentsParser.parseTaskArguments (/home/alex/projects/stability-labs/mstable/mStable-contracts/node_modules/@nomiclabs/buidler/src/internal/cli/ArgumentsParser.ts:113:38)\r\n    at main (/home/alex/projects/stability-labs/mstable/mStable-contracts/node_modules/@nomiclabs/buidler/src/internal/cli/cli.ts:128:39)\r\nerror Command failed with exit code 1.\r\ninfo Visit https://yarnpkg.com/en/docs/cli/run for documentation about this command.\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Outcome\r\n\r\nI tried running a simple test with one file and it works, so I must be missing something on the `--testfiles` flag.\r\n\r\nCould someone help me with that? How can I specify multiple?",
